description:
I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }

2. Compile using the following command:
   ajc -d subpackage Test.java

You will see a directory named "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory instead of the current directory.

Expected Behavior:
I expect the same behavior as javac, which creates the output directory in the current directory.

Observed Behavior:
Currently, ajc creates the output directory within the existing "subpackage" directory.

It will be nice to have the same behavior as javac.
